 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Subtlety Rogue Phase 1 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 305 top-ranked Subtlety Rogue DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 1 (Karazhan, Gruul's Lair and Magtheridon), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Subtlety Rogue items in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Netherblade Facemask (77%), Choker of Vile Intent (73%), Latro's Shifting Sword (66%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Karazhan, Gruul's Lair and Magtheridon."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Subtlety Rogue use in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Relentless Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Glinting Noble Topaz, Rigid Dawnstone and Shifting Nightseye in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Subtlety Rogue need in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "9 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Ferocity on head, Greater Inscription of Vengeance on shoulders, Nethercobra Leg Armor on legs and Enchant Weapon - Mongoose on weapon. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Ferocity comes from Fedryen Swiftwpear — Zangarmarsh."
  }
